    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-08-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="270"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d270">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hart</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-08-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Referring to Department’s telegraphic instructions<note n="a" xml:id="d270fna"
                        >Printed, <ref target="#pg_6">page 6</ref>.</note> concerning the protection
                    of Cuban citizens and interests by United States consular officers, Mr. Hart
                    reports that the Colombian Government has notified him that it grants the
                    request, and will instruct governors accordingly. United States consular
                    officers have been instructed by telegraph by Mr. Hart.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
